This paper deals with the minimum energy and cost required for transmitting information in a communication system, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the impact of sampling constraints on the communication system, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the possibility of adaptive sampling strategies, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
